    <div class="imageholder">
     <a rel="album" class="thickbox" href="media/images/large/ecuador---early-start.jpg">
      <img width="200" height="150" class="image_activities" alt="Ecuador" src="media/images/small/ecuador---early-start.jpg" />
     </a>
    </div>
    <!-- imageholder -->
    <div class="text_holder">
     <p class="style2">
      ECUADOR VOLCANO TRIP
     </p>
     <p>
      Dates to be  confirmed
     </p>
     <p>
      Climb 4 volcanoes in Ecuador including the highest active volcano in the world, Cotopaxi, at almost 6000m. In 2 weeks you will acclimatise on 2 volcanoes at 4200m and 4800m, then scramble up a 5125m volcano, followed by glacier training and an ascent of Cotopaxi, 5897m. Ecuador is a beautiful country with amazing landscape, great food and inspiring mountains! You also get to walk along the actual equator, at the Equatorial monument!
     </p>
     <p>
      <a class="more" href="javascript:animatedcollapse.toggle('ecuador');">
       Read More
      </a>
     </p>
     <div id="ecuador" style="display: none;">
      <p>
       DAY 1 FLY
       <br />
       DAY 2 QUITO PICK UP, VISIT THE MIDDLE OF THE WORLD MONUMENT AND PULULAHUA CRATER
       <br />
       DAY 3 HALF DAY CITY TOUR / REST IN AFTERNOON
       <br />
       DAY 4 ASCENT OF PASOCHOA, 4200M. NIGHT IN QUITO
       <br />
       DAY 5 ASCENT OF PICHINCHA, 4798M. NIGHT IN QUITO
       <br />
       DAY 6 TO ILLINIZA NORTE CAMP, 4100M
       <br />
       DAY 7 CLIMB TO SUMMIT, 5125M - NIGHT AT CAMP
       <br />
       DAY 8 DRIVE TO TAMBOPAXI LODGE, 3750M - tambopaxi.com
       <br />
       DAY 9 GLACIER TRAINING, STAY AT HUT, 4550M
       <br />
       DAY 10 ASCENT TO COTOPAXI SUMMIT, 5897M
       <br />
       DAY 11 SPARE SUMMIT DAY OR TRIP TO BANOS
       <br />
       DAY 12 DRIVE TO QUITO IN THE MORNING, AFTERNOON FREE
       <br />
       DAY 13 TRANSFER OUT
       <br />
       DAY 14 ARRIVAL
      </p>
      <p>
       Cost = £1500 per person
      </p>
     </div>
